questionListItems.title: Why am I getting billed for the entire parking duration which I originally selected even though I ended my session early?

answer.body: When you use the parking app, you'll be charged for the entire duration you selected. However, if you end your session early, the app will refund you the unused amount on a per-minute basis. It may take some time for the refund to show up on your debit or credit card statement as the refund might still be processing, so please be patient.

questionListItems.title: Parking App does not provide location of carpark T44 at Tampines St 82 where I want to park overnight. Is it because of Wilson parking here? What can I do?

answer.body: T44 have been implemented with the Electronic Parking System (EPS). EPS car parks are not included in Parking.sg as parking fees will be automatically deducted through the existing IU in the vehicle.

questionListItems.title: how do I buy the night coupon at this address Block 357 Ubi Road 3 GEKUM2

answer.body: You may select the number of hours required as per normal, and Parking.sg will automatically cap the parking charges at $5 during the night paring hours.

The app batches up multiple past parking sessions into a single card statement to reduce clutter on userâ€™s card statements. Sessions will be batched every $5 or 2 days (whichever is earlier) into bills. Hence, please do not be alarmed if you received sms alerts from your bank or noticed you were billed on days you did not park your vehicle.


Every payment is assigned with a Bill ID under your credit card statement. For re-consolidation purposes, you may refer to the respective Bill IDs and their charges from the 'BILL' tab under the History page in the app and match it against the assigned Bill ID under your credit card statement. You may find that some Bill IDs contain only one session whereas some are a combination of two or more sessions.


For more details on the batching process, you may refer to the following,

  1. You create a parking session with the app. A pending transaction appears on your card statement, on the day of the transaction, following the pattern "Parking.sg PENDING"

  2. Each time you create a new parking session, a new pending transaction appears on your card statement

  3. After 2 days, or after your pending transactions exceed $5, our billing system consolidates all those pending transactions into a single, new transaction. This is then charged to your card, and appears something like "Parking.sg Bill_abc123"

  4. Thereafter, all your individual pending transactions are cancelled.

  5. The 'Bill' tab on your parking history page shows very clearly when each bill is created, and which parking session corresponds to which bill.

questionListItems.title: I am unable to use parking app on Google pixel
questionListItems.body: I cannot even open the app on my phone.

answer.body:
Please try clearing the app's storage. Here's how:

  1. Open your phone's Settings app.

  2. Tap on Apps & notifications, and find the Parking app in the list.

  3. Tap on Storage & cache.

  4. Tap on Clear storage, then confirm your choice.

This should help resolve any issues you're experiencing with the app. If the problem persists, you may want to consider uninstalling and reinstalling the app, or contacting Parking's support team for further assistance.

questionListItems.title: How do I knew whether my motorcycle requires 2 parking lots?

answer.body: If your motorcycle has a sidecar or is larger in size, it will require two parking spots. There are also some motorcycle models that require 2 parking lots due to their size.

questionListItems.title: I left the parking lot without ending my parking session. How can I know the amount I will be charged?

answer.body: The session will automatically end once the parking duration is up, and you'll be charged accordingly. To see the amount you'll be charged, check the "History" tab in your Parking.sg app.

questionListItems.title: Why my parking app is not supported at certain places?

answer.body:
This could be because of connectivity issues with the internet.


Here are some steps to try:

  1. Check if you can access other web content without issues. If you can't, then there's probably an issue with your connection.

  2. Try deleting and reinstalling the app. Please note that your parking history will be erased when you do this, so export it first if you need it for company reimbursement or other purposes. If these steps don't work, you may email us for further assistance.

questionListItems.title: Can i park my vehicle for more than 48 hours? Because the app only allow me to select up to 24 hours. Thank you

answer.body:
Yes, you can park your vehicle for more than 24 hours. You can extend your parking session for up to 24 hours per extension, as long as there are no restrictions within the car park where you are parked.


Here's what you can do to extend your parking session:

  1. Open the app and go to the "Parking" section.

  2. Find the active session for the car park where you are parked.

  3. Tap on the "Extend" button and choose the duration of the extension.

  4. Confirm the extension and pay for the additional time. Remember to check if there are any restrictions within the car park before extending your parking session.

To update your vehicle information, you can easily delete your existing vehicle and enter the new information. Here's how:


  1. Open the app and go to the main page.

  2. Find your existing vehicle number field and tap on it.

  3. A list of your saved vehicles will appear. Click on the "X" beside the vehicle you want to delete.

  4. Once the old vehicle number is deleted, tap on the vehicle number field again and enter your new vehicle information.

That's it! Your new vehicle information is now updated in the app.

The app is design to pay for a single vehicle at any one time using a device. Having multiple digital parking may provide confusion to motorists with all the different notifications. You may wish to make use of a separate device to pay for parking for another vehicle.

questionListItems.title: Currently there are 2 parking apps on market, which is Parking@HDB (for HDB EPS parking only) and Parking.Sg (for all types of public parking).
questionListItems.body: May i check if i enter into a HDB parking that have EPS and at the same time, if i accidentally making payment via Parking.Sg, will i being immediately notify and reject by Parking.Sg for payment? Otherwise, i will prone to make duplicate car park payment. Just want to ensure, both Parking@HDB and Parking.Sg system are sync to each other simultaneously so that duplicate payment can be avoided.

answer.body:
Parking.sg is used for coupon car parks as an alternative for the paper coupons. Parking.sg does not contain any car parks that are installed with the EPS gantries, so you will not be able to trigger a parking session for a car park implemented with the EPS. Payment for car parks implemented with the EPS will be made through the existing IU.


Parking@HDB is a parking system that is currently trialed at car parks implemented with the pilot Smart Parking System. Similarly, you will not be able to trigger any parking sessions from parking.sg when entering car parks implemented with Smart Parking.

questionListItems.title: How can I buy a season parking ticket?

answer.body: If you're looking to apply for a season parking ticket, you can check out this link: https://www.ura.gov.sg/Corporate/Car-Parks/Season-Parking/Apply for more information on how to apply for one.

questionListItems.title: Cannot find carpark
questionListItems.body: I cannot find Carpark TM46 in the application.

answer.body:
Carpark TM46 has been implemented with the Electronic Parking System (EPS) and such EPS car parks are not included in the app. For such car parks, charges will be deducted from your vehicle's IU.


To find EPS car parks, you can check the official website for a list of EPS car parks. If you're unsure whether a car park is an EPS car park or not, look out for the EPS logo on the parking signages or on the parking machine.

questionListItems.title: Is handphone number linked to parking app.
questionListItems.body:
Is there a handphone number linked to parking app for checking. 

Noticed there were parking charges for days didn't park in public areas.

answer.body:
No, your handphone number is not tagged to the parking.sg app.


Regarding why you were charged for days you did not park in public areas, this is actually the intended behaviour of the app. The reason for this is that our app batches up multiple past parking sessions into a single card statement to reduce clutter on your card statements. Parking sessions payments will be batched every $5 or 2 days (whichever is earlier) into bills. So, you may find that some Bill IDs contain only one session whereas some are a combination of two or more sessions. To check your payment history, simply refer to the 'BILL' tab under the History page in the app. There, you can match the Bill IDs and their charges against the assigned Bill ID under your credit card statement. If everything matches up, then there's no need to worry!
